<br><br>
<h3>Precipitation</h3>
September has been relatively dry for the UK which is quite exceptional (Figure 12). This resulted in a dry soil which increased the rain storage capacity. The Mediterranean countries have been rather wet. The impact of the Medicane is recognized in the 1-day and 5-day precipitation sums in Greece and in particular in the countries adjacent to the Adriatic sea. The maximum 1-day sum was located in Slovenia. In Tunisia, the 5-day sum was higher than the average which was exceptional.
